item.title: Can someone unpakc these sprites/textures.rscd files?
item.dc:creator: @slaveofmen slaveofmen
item.description:
@slaveofmen wrote:

Godandjesus:

for sprites use unpacker that comes with sprite editor

i was just wondering if these sprites: ( https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,664861.0.html ) , if used with noobscape would be numbered and reconized by the game engine correctly. they have a few new sets that arent backed at the end as the newsest ones, instead thier in the middle of the sprite count. just wondering. *i had a light bulb, ill just remove the new stuff and manually re-number them myself, then ill get them packed up. *

-update-

ive deleted the new stuff, but i just wanted to make sure how many sprites are there in the sprites folder? when i was finished i got 1695 (excluding thumbs.db) am i correct?
